=== Parliamentary QA ===
Title: Vaping Prevalence Data
Date: 11 January 2023
Document Type: Parliamentary QA (Written Answer)
Topic: Vaping prevalence, survey methodology

Summary:

- Question:
  - Whether the Ministry of Health (MOH) will consider capturing information on the prevalence of vaping and other e-cigarettes in future rounds of the National Population Health Survey.

- MOH Response:
  1. Questions on vaping have already been included in the National Population Health Survey.
  2. Self-reported data may not be reliable due to the illegal nature of vaping products in Singapore.
  3. MOH is reviewing alternative methods to better estimate vaping prevalence.

Key Entities:
- Ministry of Health (MOH)
- National Population Health Survey (NPHS)

Key Concepts:
- Prevalence monitoring of vaping
- Challenges of self-reported data for illegal activities
- Exploring improved estimation methods for survey data

Author / Issuer:
Ministry of Health (MOH)
Date of Issue: January 2023
